ucien, Cecile, Herve, Jacques, Laurent, Aime.","French: topographic name designating a small wood of birches, from Occitan <i>bès</i> ‘birch tree’ (see   Besse  ), or a habitational name from (La) Bessette, the name of several places in the southern part of France.","Alternatively, an altered form of French <b>Besset</b>: topographic name, a cognate of 1 above. Altered ending reflects the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>."]}]},{"name":"Beatrice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["and French form of   Beatrix  , which was quite popular in England during the Middle Ages, and strongly revived in the 19th century. It is most famous as the name of Dante's beloved, and is borne by the elder (  b. 1988 ) of the Duke of York's daughters."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Beatrice Bassett was born in 1065, in Sussex, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Robert De Denne III."},"et":{"1065–":"1065–Surnud","1050–1088":"1050–1088","1088–1165":"1088–1165","1088–Male":"1088–Surnud","1065–Female":"1065–Surnud","1088":"1088","1165":"1165","1065":"1065","1050":"1050","about 1088":"umbes 1088","Buckhurst by Withyham, Sussex, England":"Buckhurst by Withyham, Sussex, England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"fi":{"1065–":"1065–Kuollut","1050–1088":"1050–1088","1088–1165":"1088–1165","1088–Male":"1088–Kuollut","1065–Female":"1065–Kuollut","1088":"1088","1165":"1165","1065":"1065","1050":"1050","about 1088":"noin 1088","Buckhurst by Withyham, Sussex, England":"Buckhurst by Withyham, Sussex, England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"fr":{"1065–":"1065–Décédée","1050–1088":"1050–1088","1088–1165":"1088–1165","1088–Male":"1088–Décédé","1065–Female":"1065–Décédée","1088":"1088","1165":"1165","1065":"1065","1050":"1050","about 1088":"